  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\n#### Problem\r\n\r\nAs it stands nowadays, when a notification appears/disappears in the Activity Center, the UI is updated without any sort of animation. This can (and have) confused users who might think the notification \"disappeared\" (a bug), when in reality it was the lack of UI feedback that gave that impression.\r\n\r\n#### Solution\r\n\r\nBy animating the insertion/removal of notifications, we believe users will more easily understand the sorting order when notifications are inserted/removed and, in general, be less confused about real-time updates in reaction to signals sent from the backend.\r\n\r\n### Acceptance criteria\r\n\r\nThere's no definite design yet on how the list should be animated, so it's important to align with designers what would a reasonable animation be like.",
