    "body": "I'm parking/closing this issue because I stumbled in a major bug in the Reanimated `FlatList` component, where the insertion/removal of items don't trigger the layout animation, which makes the entering/exiting of items rather clunky.\r\n\r\nThis is a known issue in Reanimated 2.3.x (https://github.com/software-mansion/react-native-reanimated/issues/2737). I wonder if upgrading Reanimated would fix it, but that's easier said than done in the Status mobile codebase, where we have a lot of outdated libs.\r\n\r\nIn the videos below, you can see the *expected vs buggy* behavior with the FlatList. Both examples can be seen by running the code in the branch https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/tree/feature/add-basic-animations-to-notifications. I pushed a single commit with all explanations to help out a future investigation https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/commit/25bf309a8af690940ff9e9d820ee1cbf50327e44.\r\n\r\nNote that the same problem happens when using Reanimated `FlatList` or just React Native `FlatList`.\r\n\r\n### Correct layout animations without Reanimated `FlatList`\r\n\r\n[working-layout-animation.webm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/210663296-6e97d99b-e5fe-4341-9a39-f39318deedd5.webm)\r\n\r\n### Clunky, no layout animations on insertion/removal with Reanimated `FlatList`\r\n\r\n[no-animations-happen.webm](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/210663319-eaa5dd53-664e-4621-97ed-f80601107d9d.webm)\r\n\r\n**cc** @briansztamfater, @Parveshdhull. I'm not sure if you're aware of this problem, so I'm copying you folks here. The bug I faced here can severely limit our ability to animate flatlists, so perhaps we should do something about it sooner rather than later.",
